  "datePublished": "2025-12-31",
  "description": "The jar method is a [sprouting](./sprout.md) technique that uses a glass jar fitted with a mesh or perforated lid to grow sprouts through repeated soaking and draining cycles. It is the most common home sprouting method because it requires no specialized equipment: a wide-mouth mason jar and a piece of cheesecloth or a mesh sprouting lid are sufficient.",
  "name": "jar method",
